WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:03.002
[OLIVER]: <i>PREVIOUSLY,</i>
<i>ON</i> SIGNED, SEALED, DELIVERED...

00:03.004 --> 00:05.304
WHEN WE WERE TALKING
ABOUT OLIVER THE OTHER DAY,

00:05.306 --> 00:06.604
HE WAS SITTING RIGHT BEHIND US?

00:06.606 --> 00:09.108
[NORMAN]: <i>WE'RE A SECRET BRANCH</i>
<i>OF THE POST OFFICE NOW?</i>

00:09.110 --> 00:10.342
"THE POSTABLES"!

00:10.344 --> 00:12.378
THE POSTMASTER GENERAL
OF THE UNITED STATES

00:12.380 --> 00:14.046
HAS INSTRUCTED ME

00:14.048 --> 00:16.782
TO CONFER UPON YOU
"THE DARK OF NIGHT" AWARD.

00:18.251 --> 00:20.386
[NORMAN]: FIRST STAMP
HONORING AN AMERICAN WOMAN?

00:20.388 --> 00:22.287
MARTHA WASHINGTON.
1902.

00:22.289 --> 00:25.557
OKAY. FIRST NATIVE AMERICAN
TO BE PUT ON A STAMP?

00:25.559 --> 00:26.625
POCAHONTAS.

00:26.627 --> 00:28.394
UH...

00:28.396 --> 00:31.063
THE YEAR 1860 IS SIGNIFICANT
FOR WHAT REASON?

00:31.065 --> 00:33.165
HMM. THE FIRST YEAR
OF THE PONY EXPRESS?

00:33.167 --> 00:35.634
MM-HMM. NAME
THREE POSTAL WORKERS

00:35.636 --> 00:38.504
WHO LATER BECAME FAMOUS
IN THE ENTERTAINMENT INDUSTRY.

00:38.506 --> 00:40.406
OHH... UM...

00:40.408 --> 00:42.141
THIS WAS THE TIE-BREAKER

00:42.143 --> 00:43.675
IN THE "FUN FACTS" CATEGORY

00:43.677 --> 00:45.277
AT LAST YEAR'S
"MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY."

00:45.279 --> 00:46.812
UM...

00:46.814 --> 00:48.614
BING CROSBY,

00:48.616 --> 00:50.115
ROCK HUDSON
AND WALT DISNEY.

00:50.117 --> 00:51.250
OH, MAN!

00:51.252 --> 00:52.618
WALT DISNEY
WORKED FOR A POST OFFICE?

00:52.620 --> 00:54.219
HE DID.

00:54.221 --> 00:55.587
IT IS A "SMALL WORLD."

00:55.589 --> 00:57.389
[ALL CHUCKLING]

00:57.391 --> 00:59.558
ABRAHAM LINCOLN WAS POSTMASTER.

00:59.560 --> 01:01.727
SO WAS HARRY TRUMAN.

01:01.729 --> 01:04.363
YES, BUT I BET
NONE OF THEM

01:04.365 --> 01:06.131
RECEIVED
THE "DARK OF NIGHT" AWARD.

01:06.133 --> 01:07.266
[OLIVER]:
OUR WORK CANNOT BE MEASURED

01:07.268 --> 01:09.168
BY ACCOLADES, MS. McINERNEY,

01:09.170 --> 01:12.071
BUT RATHER, THE SATISFACTION
OF THOSE WE SERVE.

01:12.073 --> 01:13.572
[SHANE]: WELL, IN THAT CASE,

01:13.574 --> 01:16.708
YOU MIGHT WANT TO STOP
POLISHING THOSE CUPS.

01:16.710 --> 01:18.644
WHAT DO WE HAVE?

01:20.580 --> 01:22.414
WOW...

01:22.416 --> 01:25.184
SOMEBODY IS DEFINITELY
LOOKING FOR THIS.

01:25.186 --> 01:26.251
EXQUISITE WORKMANSHIP.

01:26.253 --> 01:29.421
SHOULD BE A STAMP
OR A MARK

01:29.423 --> 01:33.625
OR "MADE BY SOMEBODY"
SOMETHING ON THE BOTTOM, BUT...

01:33.627 --> 01:35.661
SEEMS LIKE
IT'S ONE OF A KIND.

01:38.331 --> 01:39.465
OH.

01:39.467 --> 01:41.533
[♪]

01:41.535 --> 01:43.202
HMM.

01:46.473 --> 01:48.207
"HERE IT IS.

01:48.209 --> 01:50.809
"AND REMEMBER,
WHEREVER YOU KEEP YOUR TREASURE,

01:50.811 --> 01:53.145
"THAT'S WHERE YOUR HEART
WILL BE, TOO.

01:53.147 --> 01:55.414
AND THAT'S THE REAL SECRET."

01:56.716 --> 01:58.584
WAIT. WHAT--
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

01:58.586 --> 01:59.885
UH, IT MEANS

01:59.887 --> 02:01.820
THAT WHAT YOU LOVE
SAYS A LOT ABOUT WHO YOU ARE,

02:01.822 --> 02:04.456
SO, PROBABLY DOESN'T MATTER
WHO MADE THIS BOX

02:04.458 --> 02:06.191
AS MUCH AS
WHO IT WAS MADE FOR.

02:06.193 --> 02:08.527
"AND THAT'S
THE REAL SECRET"?

02:08.529 --> 02:10.629
DOES THAT MEAN THAT
THERE'S ANOTHER SECRET?

02:10.631 --> 02:12.297
LIKE A RIDDLE?

02:12.299 --> 02:13.732
OR... OR A PUZZLE!

02:13.734 --> 02:14.833
OH, MY GOSH!

02:14.835 --> 02:15.734
HMM?

02:15.736 --> 02:17.503
IT'S A PUZZLE BOX!

02:17.505 --> 02:19.805
[♪]

02:22.142 --> 02:24.510
♪ SEND ME LOVE EVERY DAY

02:24.512 --> 02:27.479
♪ AND SEND ME ON MY WAY

02:27.481 --> 02:31.717
♪ DELIVER ME
JUST DELIVER ME ♪

02:31.719 --> 02:34.820
[NORMAN]: THESE HAVE BEEN AROUND
FOR THOUSANDS OF YEARS.

02:34.822 --> 02:36.722
THEY LOOK LIKE REGULAR BOXES,

02:36.724 --> 02:38.423
BUT THE DETAIL
AND WOOD INLAY

02:38.425 --> 02:41.193
HIDE SLIDING PANELS

02:41.195 --> 02:44.329
THAT NEED TO BE OPENED
IN JUST THE RIGHT ORDER.

02:44.331 --> 02:45.564
THIS IS GOING TO TAKE SOME TIME.

02:45.566 --> 02:48.734
SO, PLEASE,
TALK AMONGST YOURSELVES.

02:48.736 --> 02:50.469
RITA?
YOU GOING TO HAVE A SNACK?

02:50.471 --> 02:52.471
NO, I'M NOT HUNGRY.
I AM...

02:52.473 --> 02:54.540
I'M SO NERVOUS
ABOUT THE PAGEANT.

02:54.542 --> 02:56.575
[SHANE]: RITA,
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.

02:56.577 --> 02:57.576
YOU'VE GOT YOUR DRESS,

02:57.578 --> 02:58.777
YOU'VE GOT
YOUR TALENT,

02:58.779 --> 03:00.846
YOU'RE GONNA ACE
THE "FUN FACTS" CATEGORY.

03:00.848 --> 03:02.781
THING IS, I CAN ONLY REMEMBER
WHAT I'VE READ,

03:02.783 --> 03:04.683
AND, OBVIOUSLY,
HAVEN'T READ ENOUGH.

03:04.685 --> 03:07.486
I MEAN, THE WHOLE
WALT DISNEY-MAIL-CARRIER-THING,

03:07.488 --> 03:09.688
THAT REALLY THREW ME.

03:09.690 --> 03:10.889
GOT IT!

03:10.891 --> 03:11.890
OH! HA.

03:11.892 --> 03:14.793
WOW.
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

03:14.795 --> 03:16.395
IT'S A MATHEMATICAL FORMULA--

03:16.397 --> 03:20.265
ONE UP, TWO DOWN, TWO UP...

03:20.267 --> 03:22.267
THREE... DOWN.

03:23.636 --> 03:25.804
SO EVEN THOUGH
THE BOX MIGHT SEEM EMPTY,

03:25.806 --> 03:29.641
THERE COULD STILL BE SOMETHING
VALUABLE LOCKED INSIDE.

03:29.643 --> 03:30.709
[CLICK]

03:30.711 --> 03:31.743
OH!

03:32.812 --> 03:34.279
AND IT'S...

03:34.281 --> 03:36.281
ANOTHER KEY.

03:37.450 --> 03:40.285
OH, I WAS REALLY
EXPECTING DIAMONDS.

03:40.287 --> 03:41.653
WELL, IT'S NOT OVER.

03:41.655 --> 03:43.388
THAT'S A KEY
TO ANOTHER BOX.

03:43.390 --> 03:44.923
A SAFE DEPOSIT BOX.

03:44.925 --> 03:46.358
OOH!

03:46.360 --> 03:47.693
MOUNTAIN HIGH BANK!

03:47.695 --> 03:49.795
OH, THAT'S 91616 ACOMA STREET.

03:49.797 --> 03:51.363
THAT IS DENVER'S SECOND-OLDEST

03:51.365 --> 03:53.298
CONTINUOUSLY-OPERATING
FINANCIAL INSTITUTION,

03:53.300 --> 03:54.766
FOUNDED IN 1897.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.235
WELL DONE.

03:56.237 --> 03:58.003
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

03:58.005 --> 03:59.271
BOOKS.

03:59.273 --> 04:00.706
BOOKS WITH PICTURES.

04:00.708 --> 04:04.009
"A COMPENDIUM OF MISCELLANEOUS
BANKING PARAPHERNALIA."

04:04.011 --> 04:05.577
MS. McINERNEY,

04:05.579 --> 04:06.878
WE WILL NEED
SOME ESSENTIAL PAPERWORK,

04:06.880 --> 04:09.448
THEN WE'LL TAKE THIS KEY,
DROP BY THE BANK.

04:09.450 --> 04:11.483
UM, BUT RITA
STILL NEEDS TO WORK

04:11.485 --> 04:12.618
ON HER FUN FACTS,

04:12.620 --> 04:13.785
AND WE HAVEN'T EVEN
CRACKED ZIP CODES

04:13.787 --> 04:15.354
OR UNIQUE
MODES OF DELIVERY.

04:15.356 --> 04:17.556
AH. THEN YOU MUST STAY.

04:17.558 --> 04:19.758
YOU GUYS ARE STILL
COMING TONIGHT, RIGHT?

04:19.760 --> 04:20.926
OH, OPENING NIGHT RECEPTION,
6:00.

04:20.928 --> 04:22.594
WE WOULDN'T MISS IT
FOR THE WORLD.

04:22.596 --> 04:24.496
[SIGHS] OH, THAT'S GREAT.
HERE'S YOUR TICKETS.

04:26.466 --> 04:28.033
THE BROWN PALACE HOTEL.
GOT IT.

04:28.035 --> 04:29.568
IT'S RIGHT ACROSS
THE STREET FROM THE BANK,

04:29.570 --> 04:30.936
SO WE CAN JUST
MEET YOU THERE.

04:30.938 --> 04:32.771
-MM-HMM.
-OH, AND DON'T BE LATE.

04:32.773 --> 04:34.606
RAMON SAYS THE SPEECHES
START RIGHT AT 7:00,

04:34.608 --> 04:36.575
AND THE DANCING
STARTS AT 8:00.

04:37.610 --> 04:38.644
DANCING?

04:38.646 --> 04:39.678
RAMON?

04:39.680 --> 04:41.313
YEAH.

04:41.315 --> 04:42.848
OH! THAT'S RIGHT.

04:42.850 --> 04:45.050
HE OWNS
YOUR OLD DANCE STUDIO, OLIVER.

04:45.052 --> 04:48.587
OH, HE'S BECOME A VERY POPULAR
LOCAL PERSONALITY THESE DAYS.

04:48.589 --> 04:49.955
HE EVEN TAUGHT THE CHA-CHA

04:49.957 --> 04:52.324
TO THE WEATHER LADY
ON THE "WAKE UP, DENVER" SHOW.

04:52.326 --> 04:54.059
OH! I GUESS YOU JUST
NEVER CAN TELL

04:54.061 --> 04:55.360
WHAT THE DAY
WILL BRING.

04:55.362 --> 04:57.362
HUH?

05:00.066 --> 05:01.600
-RYAN!
-IN HERE.

05:01.602 --> 05:02.634
WHAT DID MAMA SAY?

05:02.636 --> 05:04.303
RYAN?

05:04.305 --> 05:06.672
CHK! NE-EE-ER... OH!

05:06.674 --> 05:07.839
[THUMPS TOY DOWN]

05:07.841 --> 05:09.741
[♪]

05:10.943 --> 05:13.845
WE REALIZE, UH,
IT'S A BIT UNUSUAL, HOWEVER--

05:13.847 --> 05:15.013
NO, NO, IT'S OKAY.

05:15.015 --> 05:16.648
WE ACTUALLY SENT OUT LETTERS
LAST MONTH

05:16.650 --> 05:18.550
TELLING PEOPLE TO COME
GET THEIR STUFF

05:18.552 --> 05:20.385
FROM THE BOXES
AND MOVE IT TO THE NEW BANK,

05:20.387 --> 05:23.722
SO WE'VE HAD PEOPLE COMING IN...
[CHUCKLES]

05:23.724 --> 05:24.823
...WITHOUT KEYS,

05:24.825 --> 05:26.358
AND KEYS COMING IN WITHOUT--

05:26.360 --> 05:27.726
-[TEXT CHIMES]
-...PEOPLE.

05:27.728 --> 05:28.794
IT'S BEEN A REAL MESS.

05:28.796 --> 05:30.829
WELL, I AM SORRY
TO HEAR THAT.

05:30.831 --> 05:33.965
DO YOU KNOW IF BOX 471
HAS BEEN EMPTIED?

05:33.967 --> 05:35.834
-OR TRANSFERRED?
-471?

05:37.704 --> 05:39.438
[♪]

05:39.440 --> 05:40.906
HMM.

05:40.908 --> 05:42.774
IT'S ON THE LIST
OF DELINQUENTS,

05:42.776 --> 05:44.976
SO IT'S SCHEDULED
TO BE DRILLED OPEN

05:44.978 --> 05:46.011
AND...

05:46.013 --> 05:47.379
AUCTIONED OFF

05:47.381 --> 05:50.048
WITH ALL THE OTHER UNPAIDS
NEXT WEEK.

05:50.050 --> 05:51.850
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING
WE CAME WHEN WE DID.

05:51.852 --> 05:53.585
DO YOU KNOW HOW
WE CAN REACH THE OWNER?

05:53.587 --> 05:55.587
UH... I DON'T KNOW.

05:55.589 --> 05:58.123
THE, UH, SAFE MANAGER
QUIT LAST WEEK,

05:58.125 --> 06:00.659
SO I'M ACTUALLY FILLING IN
FOR HIM TODAY.

06:00.661 --> 06:02.694
AND WHAT A FINE JOB
YOU ARE DOING.

06:02.696 --> 06:03.595
THANK YOU.

06:05.465 --> 06:07.799
WELL, YOU WANNA GO DOWN
AND OPEN IT NOW?

06:07.801 --> 06:08.900
YES.

06:08.902 --> 06:10.936
OH! OH, OKAY.

06:10.938 --> 06:12.604
[KEYS RATTLING]

06:12.606 --> 06:14.005
ALRIGHTY. LET'S GO.

06:15.441 --> 06:17.676
IT TAKES A LOT OF HALLS
TO GET DOWN HERE, HUH?

06:17.678 --> 06:19.411
YEAH, WE GOT
MYRIADS OF 'EM.

06:19.413 --> 06:21.680
ACTUALLY,
THE WORD "MYRIAD"

06:21.682 --> 06:22.914
IS AN INCLUSIVE NOUN--

06:22.916 --> 06:24.649
HERE WE GO.

06:24.651 --> 06:26.118
[VAULT DOOR RUMBLING]

06:28.788 --> 06:29.988
[HALTINGLY]:
IN THERE?

06:31.624 --> 06:33.725
HMM.

06:36.929 --> 06:38.096
[MOTHER, CALLING NEARBY]:
RYAN...

06:38.098 --> 06:40.732
RYAN?

06:42.101 --> 06:43.468
RYAN...

06:43.470 --> 06:46.037
[♪]

06:47.774 --> 06:51.009
IT'LL TAKE YOUR KEY AND MINE
TO OPEN UP THE BOX.

06:51.011 --> 06:54.613
LET ME JUST SEE IF I CAN FIND
THE RIGHT ONE...

06:54.615 --> 06:57.048
[ALARM BLARING]

06:57.050 --> 06:59.117
UH, WHAT'S HAPPENING?

06:59.119 --> 07:00.819
OH, UH, I THINK WE SHOULD
PROBABLY MOVE TOWARDS THE--

07:00.821 --> 07:02.788
OH! HEY-- OH!

07:02.790 --> 07:03.822
OLIVER...

07:03.824 --> 07:04.790
[THUD]

07:04.792 --> 07:06.057
NO!

07:06.059 --> 07:08.560
NO. NO-NO-NO-NO-NO!

07:08.562 --> 07:10.495
[SOBS]: NO...

07:10.497 --> 07:12.697
OH, DEAR.

07:12.699 --> 07:14.800
[FIRE ALARM RINGING]

07:14.802 --> 07:18.570
RYAN? RYAN.

07:18.572 --> 07:19.871
[RECORDED MESSAGE]:
<i>ALL CUSTOMERS AND EMPLOYEES</i>

07:19.873 --> 07:22.073
<i>MUST EXIT</i>
<i>THE BUILDING IMMEDIATELY.</i>

07:22.075 --> 07:25.043
<i>DO NOT STOP</i>
<i>TO RETRIEVE PERSONAL BELONGINGS.</i>

07:25.045 --> 07:27.145
[PHONE RINGING]

07:29.215 --> 07:31.116
HELLO?

07:31.118 --> 07:32.551
HI, DADDY.

07:32.553 --> 07:35.554
OH, UH, I'M SORRY,
I AM NOT YOUR FATHER.

07:35.556 --> 07:36.721
RYAN?

07:36.723 --> 07:38.590
GET OVER HERE
NOW. NOW!

07:38.592 --> 07:39.890
[OLIVER]: <i>NO, NO, NO. WAIT!</i>

07:39.892 --> 07:41.827
<i>WAIT. RYAN? RYAN, RYAN...</i>
<i>HELLO?</i>

07:41.829 --> 07:43.728
HELLO?

07:43.730 --> 07:45.028
[RECORDED MESSAGE]:
<i>ALL CUSTOMERS AND EMPLOYEES</i>

07:45.030 --> 07:47.199
<i>MUST EXIT</i>
<i>THE BUILDING IMMEDIATELY.</i>

07:47.201 --> 07:50.101
<i>DO NOT STOP</i>
<i>TO RETRIEVE PERSONAL BELONGINGS.</i>

07:50.103 --> 07:52.070
[ELECTRICITY THUDS]

07:53.172 --> 07:54.039
WHOA.

07:56.242 --> 07:58.810
[♪]

08:08.888 --> 08:11.823
OH, WOW.
THAT IS SOME SASH.

08:11.825 --> 08:13.558
OH. THANK YOU.

08:13.560 --> 08:15.060
I COULDN'T DECIDE
WHETHER OR NOT

08:15.062 --> 08:16.194
I SHOULD WEAR
MY HAIR UP OR DOWN.

08:16.196 --> 08:18.096
YES.

08:18.098 --> 08:19.264
UM...

08:19.266 --> 08:20.866
I CAN'T DO MY TIE.

08:20.868 --> 08:22.033
OH. HERE.

08:22.035 --> 08:24.870
I CAN HELP YOU.

08:26.672 --> 08:27.873
OH.

08:27.875 --> 08:28.974
I, UH...

08:30.543 --> 08:32.644
I-I-- I'M--
I'M NOT REALLY...

08:32.646 --> 08:34.513
VERY GOOD AT DOING, UM,

08:34.515 --> 08:37.148
DOING OTHER PEOPLE'S TIES.

08:39.185 --> 08:41.987
UH, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I HAVE AN IDEA.

08:41.989 --> 08:43.788
OH.

08:43.790 --> 08:45.290
[MUSIC FILTERING
FROM HEADPHONES]

08:45.292 --> 08:46.791
[SHANE SIGHS]
NOTHING.

08:46.793 --> 08:48.994
NO CELL SERVICE,
NO INTERNET.

08:48.996 --> 08:52.697
♪ ENNH...
MM-MM, ENNH... ♪

08:54.300 --> 08:56.201
♪ DUN

08:56.203 --> 08:58.303
♪ DOO-OO-OO

09:00.907 --> 09:02.274
HEY.

09:02.276 --> 09:03.642
WHAT'S SHAKIN'?

09:03.644 --> 09:04.776
WELL, JASON,

09:04.778 --> 09:06.711
IT APPEARS
WE ARE ALL LOCKED IN A VAULT

09:06.713 --> 09:09.047
AND NO ONE IS ANSWERING

09:09.049 --> 09:10.649
THE RED PHONE.

09:10.651 --> 09:11.749
WELL, THAT'S 'CAUSE

09:11.751 --> 09:13.618
THEY'RE PROBABLY ALL OUTSIDE
AT THE FIRE DRILL.

09:13.620 --> 09:14.686
BANKS DON'T
HAVE FIRE DRILLS

09:14.688 --> 09:15.921
AT 5:00...

09:15.923 --> 09:17.756
...ON FRIDAY NIGHT.
YOU MUST HAVE--

09:17.758 --> 09:18.990
RECEIVED "NEW EMPLOYEE"
TRAINING ONCE.

09:18.992 --> 09:20.058
THAT MIGHT BE HELPFUL.

09:20.060 --> 09:21.192
OH, YEAH. LAST WEEK.

09:23.930 --> 09:25.263
OKAY.

09:25.265 --> 09:26.765
JASON.

09:26.767 --> 09:29.034
I WANT YOU TO REMEMBER
ALL-L-L-L THE WAY BACK

09:29.036 --> 09:30.335
TO LAST WEEK

09:30.337 --> 09:31.937
AND SEE IF ANYBODY
SAID ANYTHING ABOUT,

09:31.939 --> 09:34.172
OH... BREATHING
IN A LOCKED VAULT,

09:34.174 --> 09:35.240
FOR EXAMPLE?

09:36.809 --> 09:38.743
YES.

09:39.845 --> 09:41.179
AND...?

09:41.181 --> 09:43.148
OH. UH...

09:43.150 --> 09:44.983
ONCE IT'S CLOSED...

09:44.985 --> 09:47.085
IT AUTOMATICALLY SEALS

09:47.087 --> 09:50.055
AND THEN IT PROBABLY
CAN'T BE OPENED FOR 12 HOURS.

09:50.057 --> 09:51.590
"PROBABLY" OR "DEFINITELY"?

09:51.592 --> 09:53.792
DEFINITELY PROBABLY.
I DON'T KNOW. PROBABLY?

09:53.794 --> 09:54.826
IT'S AN OLD BANK.

09:54.828 --> 09:56.127
PRESS ON, JASON.

09:56.129 --> 09:57.629
BUT...

09:57.631 --> 10:00.832
THERE'S UP TO 13 HOURS
OF AIR

10:00.834 --> 10:03.668
JUST IN CASE SOMEBODY DOES
GET TRAPPED IN THE VAULT.

10:03.670 --> 10:04.669
THERE YOU GO.

10:04.671 --> 10:06.037
13 HOURS.

10:06.039 --> 10:07.205
THAT'S MORE THAN ENOUGH TIME

10:07.207 --> 10:09.608
TO RESCUE SOMEBODY
LOCKED IN A VAULT.

10:09.610 --> 10:11.977
THERE ARE
THREE OF US BREATHING.

10:11.979 --> 10:13.278
WELL, THAT'S DEBATABLE.

10:13.280 --> 10:15.080
MY POINT IS,
MS. McINERNEY,

10:15.082 --> 10:18.216
13 HOURS TRANSLATES
TO 4 HOURS, 20 MINUTES OF AIR

10:18.218 --> 10:19.317
FOR EACH BREATHER.

10:20.753 --> 10:23.855
NOT TO MENTION,
NOBODY KNOWS WE'RE DOWN HERE.

10:23.857 --> 10:25.857
[SIGHS]

10:27.193 --> 10:30.662
[SHANE]: ARE YOU ACTUALLY
WRITING YOUR WILL?

10:30.664 --> 10:32.263
NO.

10:32.265 --> 10:34.199
TIMES SUCH AS THIS,

10:34.201 --> 10:36.701
UH, PROVIDE ONE WITH A...

10:36.703 --> 10:38.136
A CERTAIN CLARITY.

10:38.138 --> 10:39.771
[SNICKERING]

10:39.773 --> 10:40.939
[SHANE]: OLIVER,
THIS IS VERY SERIOUS.

10:40.941 --> 10:42.007
I KNOW.

10:42.009 --> 10:43.642
WE COULD
RUN OUT OF AIR

10:43.644 --> 10:45.410
AND STOP... BREATHING.

10:45.412 --> 10:47.345
I DON'T BELIEVE
THAT'S GOING TO HAPPEN.

10:47.347 --> 10:50.415
HOWEVER,
WHAT I AM CONCERNED ABOUT...

10:51.851 --> 10:55.120
...THAT JASON'S BATTERIES
WILL BE RUNNING OUT SOON,

10:55.122 --> 10:56.421
AND WE WILL BE FORCED
ONCE AGAIN

10:56.423 --> 10:58.289
TO CONVERSE WITH HIM.

10:58.291 --> 11:00.325
[LAUGHS]

11:00.327 --> 11:02.927
YOU'RE RIGHT.

11:02.929 --> 11:04.396
COULD BE WORSE.

11:04.398 --> 11:06.898
I COULD BE
AT THE BROWN PALACE,

11:06.900 --> 11:10.001
DANCING THE PASO DOBLE
WITH <i>RAMON.</i>

11:10.003 --> 11:13.104
I WOULD NOT ALLOW THAT
TO HAPPEN TO YOU.

11:15.074 --> 11:16.408
[CHUCKLING]

11:16.410 --> 11:17.676
UGH.

11:17.678 --> 11:18.810
I'VE GOT TO DO SOMETHING

11:18.812 --> 11:20.779
TO KEEP MYSELF
FROM GOING CRAZY.

11:20.781 --> 11:23.081
LET'S PLAY A GAME.

11:23.083 --> 11:24.949
I WILL SAY SOMETHING,

11:24.951 --> 11:28.853
AND YOU SAY THE FIRST THING
THAT COMES INTO YOUR HEAD.

11:28.855 --> 11:30.055
READY?

11:30.057 --> 11:31.122
NO.

11:31.124 --> 11:32.691
DOOR.

11:34.226 --> 11:35.860
KNOB.

11:35.862 --> 11:36.861
WINDOW.

11:38.030 --> 11:39.097
WASHER.

11:39.099 --> 11:40.398
-CAR.
-...BURATOR.

11:40.400 --> 11:41.966
THAT'S A NORMAN ANSWER!

11:41.968 --> 11:42.901
-[BOTH LAUGHING]
-I KNOW.

11:45.838 --> 11:47.305
[SIGHS]

11:47.307 --> 11:49.074
-APPLES.
-AUTUMN.

11:49.076 --> 11:50.375
SUMMER.

11:50.377 --> 11:52.110
CREEK.

11:54.980 --> 11:56.448
AHEM.

11:56.450 --> 11:59.918
I USED TO FLOAT ON
BOULDER CREEK ON AN INNERTUBE

11:59.920 --> 12:01.953
IN THE SUMMER
WHEN I WAS A KID.

12:01.955 --> 12:03.788
WOW. YOU WERE A KID.

12:03.790 --> 12:04.823
HUH.

12:04.825 --> 12:06.091
IS THIS GAME OVER?

12:06.093 --> 12:07.492
-NO. FOREST.
-PEACEFUL.

12:07.494 --> 12:09.027
-APRIL.
-PARIS.

12:09.029 --> 12:09.994
-CHRISTMAS.
-HOLLY.

12:11.130 --> 12:13.064
"HOLLY" THE PLANT,

12:13.066 --> 12:14.733
OR "HOLLY" YOUR...

12:16.368 --> 12:19.003
...WIFE.

12:20.873 --> 12:23.875
[♪]

12:31.851 --> 12:34.119
[PIANO MUSIC PLAYING,
PEOPLE CHATTING]

12:34.121 --> 12:36.154
[CLINK]

12:42.061 --> 12:44.062
WOW.

12:45.965 --> 12:47.098
OH-OH.

12:47.100 --> 12:49.300
EVERYBODY'S
COMPLETELY DRESSED.

12:49.302 --> 12:51.035
OH, NO, NO, NO, WAIT.

12:51.037 --> 12:52.137
OLIVER WILL
TIE YOUR TIE.

12:52.139 --> 12:53.538
WE JUST NEED
TO FIND HIM.

12:53.540 --> 12:54.773
HE'S GOTTA BE
IN HERE SOMEWHERE.

12:54.775 --> 12:56.107
R-RITA!

12:56.109 --> 12:58.443
SENORITA RITA.

12:58.445 --> 13:01.279
OH! RAMON. HI.

13:01.281 --> 13:02.280
WELL...

13:02.282 --> 13:04.783
YOU LOOK

13:04.785 --> 13:06.484
RAVISHING.

13:06.486 --> 13:08.453
[NERVOUS CHUCKLE]

13:08.455 --> 13:10.321
AND THIS GENTLEMAN
IS YOUR...

13:10.323 --> 13:11.389
BROTHER?

13:11.391 --> 13:13.858
NO, NO, NO.
THIS IS MY NORMAN.

13:13.860 --> 13:16.094
I MEAN, NORMAN IS MINE--
I MEAN...

13:16.096 --> 13:18.329
NORMAN IS MY CO-WORKER,

13:18.331 --> 13:20.198
AND HE NEEDS A TIE.

13:20.200 --> 13:21.933
NO, I MEAN, HE HAS A TIE,
HE JUST NEEDS A TIE--

13:21.935 --> 13:22.934
HE JUST
NEEDS IT TIED.

13:22.936 --> 13:24.335
SAY NO MORE.
ALLOW ME.

13:24.337 --> 13:26.204
OKAY.

13:26.206 --> 13:27.806
[CHUCKLES] OH...

13:27.808 --> 13:30.475
LITTLE TINY MAILBOXES!

13:30.477 --> 13:32.343
THAT'S...
THAT'S VERY CHARMING.

13:32.345 --> 13:34.078
OLIVER GAVE IT TO ME
FOR CHRISTMAS.

13:34.080 --> 13:35.980
-OLLYVEER? O'TOOLE?
-YEAH.

13:35.982 --> 13:37.081
-MM-HMM.
-THE POSTAL MAN?

13:37.083 --> 13:38.149
OLIVER IS OUR BOSS.

13:38.151 --> 13:39.818
HE AND SHANE
SHOULD BE HERE

13:39.820 --> 13:40.885
ANY MINUTE NOW.

13:40.887 --> 13:42.220
AH, YES,
THE BEAUTIFUL SHANE.

13:42.222 --> 13:43.321
I REMEMBER THEM.

13:43.323 --> 13:44.889
SUCH A BEAUTIFUL COUPLE.

13:44.891 --> 13:47.025
WELL, ACTUALLY,
THEY'RE NOT A COUPLE.

13:47.027 --> 13:49.561
WELL, WHAT DO WE TRULY KNOW
OF LOVE, NORMANDO?

13:49.563 --> 13:50.595
WELL--

13:50.597 --> 13:51.830
SHH.

13:51.832 --> 13:53.898
VOILA.

13:53.900 --> 13:55.133
OH. WOW.

13:55.135 --> 13:56.501
I HAVE NEVER SEEN
ANYONE TIE A TIE

13:56.503 --> 13:57.969
THE WAY YOU JUST TIED
THAT TIE.

13:57.971 --> 13:59.304
OF COURSE NOT.

13:59.306 --> 14:01.506
NOW, IF YOU WILL
PLEASE EXCUSE ME.

14:01.508 --> 14:03.441
NORMANDO... A PLEASURE.

14:06.579 --> 14:09.047
HE'S WEIRD.

14:10.382 --> 14:14.185
[SHANE]: I THINK IT'S TOO LATE
TO TEACH JASON ENGLISH.

14:14.187 --> 14:17.088
BUT NOT TOO LATE
TO TEACH HIM SOMETHING.

14:19.525 --> 14:21.459
JASON?

14:24.897 --> 14:27.932
SO WHAT'S SO IMPORTANT ABOUT
WHAT'S IN THIS BOX, ANYWAY?

14:27.934 --> 14:29.400
OH, WE DON'T KNOW,
BUT SOMEONE

14:29.402 --> 14:31.135
CONSIDERED IT IMPORTANT ENOUGH

14:31.137 --> 14:33.104
TO KEEP IT SAFE
AND HIDE THE KEY.

14:33.106 --> 14:35.540
NOT IMPORTANT ENOUGH
TO PAY THE RENT ON THE BOX.

14:35.542 --> 14:38.376
EVERYTHING THAT PASSES THROUGH
THE U.S. POSTAL SYSTEM

14:38.378 --> 14:41.312
IS IMPORTANT TO SOMEONE.

14:41.314 --> 14:42.647
TO SOME STRANGER.

14:42.649 --> 14:44.215
SO WHAT?

14:44.217 --> 14:47.118
"IF ONE IS CALLED
TO BE A STREETSWEEPER,

14:47.120 --> 14:50.588
"THEN ONE MUST SWEEP STREETS
EVEN AS MICHELANGELO PAINTED,

14:50.590 --> 14:53.057
OR BEETHOVEN COMPOSED MUSIC--"

14:53.059 --> 14:54.592
HEY. HEY!

14:54.594 --> 14:57.328
OH, MY GOODNESS.
JASON!

14:57.330 --> 14:59.364
WELL DONE.
FANTASTIC.

14:59.366 --> 15:01.499
[♪]

15:08.540 --> 15:10.308
[CHUCKLING]

15:13.445 --> 15:15.413
MS. McINERNEY?

15:16.515 --> 15:18.483
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO DO THE HONORS?

15:20.252 --> 15:22.587
YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES,
THEY ACTUALLY COME UP EMPTY.

15:26.191 --> 15:27.425
[LOCK CLICKS]

15:27.427 --> 15:29.460
[LID CREAKS]

15:30.663 --> 15:32.997
WELL, NO DIAMONDS FOR RITA.

15:32.999 --> 15:34.599
WHAT ARE THEY?

15:37.102 --> 15:38.336
LETTERS.

15:38.338 --> 15:40.571
NO... ENVELOPES,

15:40.573 --> 15:41.673
NO RETURN ADDRESSES,

15:41.675 --> 15:44.609
JUST A WHOLE BUNCH
OF LETTERS.

15:44.611 --> 15:47.145
IT'LL TAKE US A WHILE
TO READ THROUGH ALL OF THESE.

15:47.147 --> 15:49.647
PROBABLY, TWO TO THREE HOURS...

15:51.417 --> 15:53.985
PROBABLY.

15:53.987 --> 15:55.420
[OLIVER]: JANUARY 2ND, '08.

15:55.422 --> 15:56.587
"DEAR FRIEND...

15:56.589 --> 15:58.156
"MAY I CALL YOU KATHERINE?

15:58.158 --> 15:59.624
"HAPPY NEW YEAR,

15:59.626 --> 16:02.093
"ALTHOUGH IT'S DIFFICULT
TO IMAGINE

16:02.095 --> 16:05.129
"A NEW YEAR THAT COULD EVER
SURPASS MY HAPPIEST NEW YEAR'S.

16:05.131 --> 16:07.365
"I MUST CONFESS SOMETHING
ABOUT THAT NIGHT--

16:07.367 --> 16:08.665
"I HAD NO INTENTION OF WALKING

16:08.667 --> 16:12.203
"FROM THE EXQUISITE SILENCE
OF THE SNOW-COVERED CENTRAL PARK

16:12.205 --> 16:13.471
"ALL THE WAY DOWN

16:13.473 --> 16:17.041
"TO THE ROLLICKING FESTIVITIES
OF 42ND STREET.

16:17.043 --> 16:19.510
"BUT SURELY SOMETHING
LED ME THERE TO YOU.

16:19.512 --> 16:21.245
"IN FACT,

16:21.247 --> 16:24.582
"PROVIDENCE ITSELF HAS MADE
SOMETHING OF A BELIEVER OF ME,

16:24.584 --> 16:26.351
"BECAUSE NOTHING LESS
THAN A MIRACLE

16:26.353 --> 16:28.553
"COULD HAVE DIRECTED MY EYES
TO YOUR EYES

16:28.555 --> 16:31.189
"OR MY LIPS TO YOUR LIPS

16:31.191 --> 16:32.657
"AT THAT MOMENT

16:32.659 --> 16:35.460
"WHEN THAT BEAUTIFUL BALL
DROPPED AT MIDNIGHT

16:35.462 --> 16:39.163
AND EVERYTHING OLD
BECAME NEW ONCE AGAIN."

16:42.001 --> 16:44.469
[♪]

16:48.173 --> 16:49.774
"ALTHOUGH
THEY WERE NOT THE FIRST LIPS

16:49.776 --> 16:51.476
"I HAVE EVER KISSED,

16:51.478 --> 16:54.345
UNTIL WE MEET AGAIN,
THEY WILL BE THE LAST."

16:54.347 --> 16:55.413
[HE CHUCKLES]

16:55.415 --> 16:57.013
"I HOPE YOU WILL WRITE TO ME.

16:57.015 --> 16:59.517
"THINGS MOVE SO QUICKLY
IN THE WORLD THESE DAYS,

16:59.519 --> 17:00.685
"AND I AM A GREAT BELIEVER

17:00.687 --> 17:02.453
"IN THE POWER OF A LETTER

17:02.455 --> 17:05.023
TO REMIND US OF WHAT LASTS."

17:05.025 --> 17:06.724
[♪]

17:12.097 --> 17:15.500
"YOURS SINCERELY,
JONATHAN FROM NEW YORK."

17:15.502 --> 17:17.135
WOW!

17:17.137 --> 17:19.771
A LETTER-WRITER WHO PICKS UP
WOMEN IN TIMES SQUARE.

17:19.773 --> 17:24.642
A ROMANTIC WHO BEFRIENDED
A LADY LOST IN THE CROWD.

17:26.178 --> 17:28.079
[SHE CHUCKLES]

17:28.081 --> 17:30.481
"FEBRUARY 4TH, '08--

17:30.483 --> 17:31.716
"DEAR JONATHAN,

17:31.718 --> 17:33.051
"HOW LONG IT'S BEEN

17:33.053 --> 17:34.419
"SINCE I RECEIVED A LETTER,

17:34.421 --> 17:36.354
"A REAL LETTER,

17:36.356 --> 17:38.322
"AND NEVER ONE LIKE THIS.

17:38.324 --> 17:41.092
"THIS HAS ALREADY BEEN
A YEAR OF FIRSTS FOR ME--

17:41.094 --> 17:43.561
"MY FIRST TRIP TO NEW YORK,

17:43.563 --> 17:45.830
MY FIRST DATE WITH A STRANGER,
AND YES, IT'S TRUE..."

17:47.299 --> 17:49.700
"...MY FIRST KISS."

17:49.702 --> 17:51.235
HMM.

17:51.237 --> 17:53.171
"I KNOW IT'S HARD TO BELIEVE
AT MY AGE,

17:53.173 --> 17:55.506
"BUT I HAVE NEVER BEEN
CONSIDERED A GREAT BEAUTY

17:55.508 --> 17:57.742
"AND I GUESS
I'VE ALWAYS BEHAVED

17:57.744 --> 18:00.144
"AS IF I BELIEVED IT
TO BE TRUE.

18:00.146 --> 18:02.313
"THAT NIGHT,
STANDING IN THE COLD,

18:02.315 --> 18:03.748
"SURROUNDED BY
A THOUSAND HAPPY STRANGERS,

18:03.750 --> 18:05.850
"I FELT FREE AND FRESH,

18:05.852 --> 18:09.120
"AND PERHAPS
IT WAS AT THAT MOMENT

18:09.122 --> 18:12.090
THAT YOU SAW ME
FEELING BEAUTIFUL."

18:12.092 --> 18:15.093
[♪]

18:18.130 --> 18:22.100
"AND THEN YOU WALKED UP
AND MADE IT SO.

18:22.102 --> 18:23.534
"WE LIVE SO FAR APART,

18:23.536 --> 18:26.170
"THE DAY WE MEET AGAIN
MAY NOT COME,

18:26.172 --> 18:30.108
"BUT I SHALL NEVER FORGET
THE HOURS WE SPENT--

18:30.110 --> 18:31.742
"WALKING UP FIFTH AVENUE,

18:31.744 --> 18:33.578
"SIPPING TEA AT THE PLAZA,

18:33.580 --> 18:36.714
"AND RIDING THE CARRIAGE
IN THE PARK,

18:36.716 --> 18:39.417
"DANCING UNDER THE STARS...

18:39.419 --> 18:41.519
"KISSING GOODBYE.

18:41.521 --> 18:43.387
"I HOPE YOU WILL WRITE AGAIN

18:43.389 --> 18:44.555
"AND TELL ME MORE
OF YOUR LIFE.

18:44.557 --> 18:48.292
"THANK YOU
FOR WALKING INTO MINE.

18:48.294 --> 18:49.660
YOURS SINCERELY,
KATHERINE."

18:49.662 --> 18:52.463
[♪]

18:52.465 --> 18:55.633
UH, JASON,
UH, WHAT DO WE HAVE SO FAR?

18:55.635 --> 18:56.734
AHEM.

18:56.736 --> 18:59.504
NEW YORK,
TIMES SQUARE,

18:59.506 --> 19:01.906
NEW YEAR'S EVE '08,

19:01.908 --> 19:04.609
THE PLAZA,
CENTRAL PARK,

19:04.611 --> 19:07.145
SOMEBODY NAMED PROVIDENCE,

19:07.147 --> 19:09.480
AND AN UGLY CHICK
NAMED KATHERINE.

19:09.482 --> 19:11.382
SHE'S NOT UGLY.
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

19:11.384 --> 19:12.517
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

19:12.519 --> 19:13.885
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL TO JONATHAN!

19:13.887 --> 19:15.286
YEAH, THE GUY
WHO COULDN'T GET

19:15.288 --> 19:16.586
A DATE
ON NEW YEAR'S EVE.

19:16.588 --> 19:19.690
YES, WELL, HE CERTAINLY SEEMS
LIKE A GENTLEMAN TO ME,

19:19.692 --> 19:23.261
SOMEONE I WOULDN'T MIND
TAKING TO LUNCH SOMEDAY.

19:23.263 --> 19:24.829
LUNCH...

19:24.831 --> 19:27.431
I'M SO HUNGRY.

19:30.669 --> 19:32.270
COOL!

19:32.272 --> 19:34.438
I USUALLY TAKE MY NAP
AFTER LUNCH, TOO, SO, UH--

19:34.440 --> 19:35.473
[SHANE]: GOOD!

19:35.475 --> 19:37.508
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

19:37.510 --> 19:40.244
[♪]

19:47.219 --> 19:48.853
[RITA]: ANY SIGN OF THEM?

19:48.855 --> 19:52.390
NO. BUT I THINK
I SEE OLIVER'S CAR

19:52.392 --> 19:54.192
PARKED OVER THERE,
BY THE BANK.

19:54.194 --> 19:55.426
[♪]

19:55.428 --> 19:56.694
OH, NO.

19:56.696 --> 19:59.197
THEY'RE ABOUT TO
START THE PROGRAM.

19:59.199 --> 20:01.432
VERY ATYPICAL.

20:01.434 --> 20:03.267
OH, OLIVER'S
MORE RELIABLE THAN...

20:03.269 --> 20:05.236
THAN A...

20:05.238 --> 20:06.637
THAN A MULE
DELIVERING MAIL BAGS

20:06.639 --> 20:08.439
TO THE BOTTOM
OF THE GRAND CANYON.

20:08.441 --> 20:11.375
YEAH! I MEAN, I WASN'T
GONNA SAY THAT, BUT, YEAH!

20:11.377 --> 20:12.710
[RAMON]:
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

20:12.712 --> 20:13.945
MAY I HAVE
YOUR ATTENTION, PLEASE?

20:13.947 --> 20:15.446
WILL OUR PAGEANT CONTESTANTS

20:15.448 --> 20:17.348
KINDLY TAKE THEIR PLACES
ON THE STAGE?

20:17.350 --> 20:18.616
OH, UH, GO AHEAD.

20:18.618 --> 20:19.884
I'LL KEEP
AN EYE OUT FOR THEM,

20:19.886 --> 20:21.219
AND I'LL WATCH
YOUR PURSE.

20:21.221 --> 20:22.653
OKAY. THANK YOU.

20:23.822 --> 20:27.758
[♪]

20:29.861 --> 20:32.296
[OLIVER]: "DEAR KATHERINE--

20:32.298 --> 20:34.632
"AS I SIT HERE AT MY DESK
IN THE FLATIRON BUILDING,

20:34.634 --> 20:36.701
"I LOOK OUT THE WINDOW
AND REALIZE

20:36.703 --> 20:38.436
"THAT ALL THAT MANKIND
CAN BUILD

20:38.438 --> 20:40.905
"WITH STEEL AND GLASS
AND STONE

20:40.907 --> 20:42.873
"CAN NEVER COMPARE TO A LIFE

20:42.875 --> 20:46.310
"BUILT ON A FOUNDATION
OF LOVE FOR ANOTHER

20:46.312 --> 20:49.013
AND FAITH IN
SOMETHING GREATER THAN ONESELF."

20:49.015 --> 20:50.982
[♪]

20:55.687 --> 20:57.755
"YOU SPOKE OF THOSE THINGS
AS THE SUN CAME UP

20:57.757 --> 20:59.290
"ON NEW YEAR'S DAY,

20:59.292 --> 21:01.926
"AND EVEN IF
WE CAN'T KEEP DANCING...

21:01.928 --> 21:04.996
"I WOULD LIKE TO KEEP
THAT CONVERSATION GOING.

21:04.998 --> 21:06.697
"WRITE TO ME.

21:06.699 --> 21:08.666
YOURS, JONATHAN."

21:09.835 --> 21:11.769
"MARCH 17TH, '08.

21:11.771 --> 21:13.304
"DEAR JONATHAN,

21:13.306 --> 21:16.274
"I DON'T BELIEVE
IN COINCIDENCE OR FATE.

21:16.276 --> 21:19.310
"I BELIEVE OUR LIVES
HAVE PURPOSE AND MEANING.

21:19.312 --> 21:22.613
"I BELIEVE IT IS NO ACCIDENT
THAT WE MET,

21:22.615 --> 21:24.282
OR EVEN THAT WE BOTH WORK
IN..."

21:24.284 --> 21:27.285
[LAUGHS]
"...TRIANGULAR BUILDINGS.

21:27.287 --> 21:29.420
[BOTH LAUGHING]

21:29.422 --> 21:31.656
"YES, I HAVE TAKEN A JOB

21:31.658 --> 21:34.558
"AT THE BEAUTIFUL
BROWN PALACE HOTEL.

21:34.560 --> 21:37.762
"IT IS DENVER'S ELEGANT,
THREE-CORNERED LANDMARK

21:37.764 --> 21:39.363
"AND REMINDS ME

21:39.365 --> 21:42.533
"THAT TWO OF ANYTHING IS
ALWAYS STRONGER WITH A THIRD--

21:42.535 --> 21:46.370
"A CORD OF THREE STRANDS
IS NEVER BROKEN,

21:46.372 --> 21:50.408
"A BUILDING OF THREE CORNERS
CAN WITHSTAND THE WINDS,

21:50.410 --> 21:53.811
"AND TWO HEARTS
JOINED BY A GREATER ONE

21:53.813 --> 21:56.714
"CAN WITHSTAND ANYTHING.

21:56.716 --> 22:00.518
YOURS, KATHERINE."

22:00.520 --> 22:02.019
"DEAR KATHERINE,

22:02.021 --> 22:04.855
"I TOLD YOU
THAT I KEEP AN OFFICE

22:04.857 --> 22:06.090
"IN THE FLATIRON BUILDING,

22:06.092 --> 22:08.059
"BUT I NEGLECTED THE DETAILS

22:08.061 --> 22:10.494
"FOR FEAR IT MIGHT
SEEM TRIVIAL TO YOU,

22:10.496 --> 22:12.029
"A LADY OF LETTERS AND BOOKS.

22:12.031 --> 22:14.498
"I AM A JOURNALIST,
A SPORTSWRITER,

22:14.500 --> 22:16.567
"WHO TRAVELS AROUND,
WRITING ABOUT...

22:16.569 --> 22:17.668
BASEBALL."

22:17.670 --> 22:19.737
BASEBALL?

22:19.739 --> 22:21.706
I WOULD'VE THOUGHT...

22:21.708 --> 22:23.474
"TO MANY,
BASEBALL IS JUST A GAME

22:23.476 --> 22:24.975
"PLAYED BY OVERGROWN BOYS,

22:24.977 --> 22:26.275
"BUT IN THAT GAME,

22:26.277 --> 22:28.779
"I SEE THE BEST
AND, SOMETIMES, THE WORST

22:28.781 --> 22:30.081
OF OUR COUNTRY
AND ITS MEN."

22:30.083 --> 22:31.949
"DEAREST JONATHAN,

22:31.951 --> 22:34.618
I ATTENDED MY FIRST
BASEBALL GAME LAST NIGHT."

22:34.620 --> 22:36.087
[CHUCKLING] WOW.

22:36.089 --> 22:39.957
"I SAT BEHIND HOME BASE
AND TRIED TO SEE WHAT YOU SEE,

22:39.959 --> 22:41.459
"BUT THE TRUTH IS,

22:41.461 --> 22:42.593
"ALL I COULD IMAGINE

22:42.595 --> 22:44.962
"WAS YOU SITTING NEXT TO ME,

22:44.964 --> 22:47.698
MAKING JOKES AND SINGING ALONG
WITH THE BAND."

22:47.700 --> 22:49.133
[OLIVER, READING]:
"AND I AM EVERY DAY INSPIRED

22:49.135 --> 22:51.469
"BY THE EVERYDAY HEROES
WHO TAKE UP BAT AND BALL

22:51.471 --> 22:53.104
"AND SWING FOR THE STARS.

22:53.106 --> 22:54.805
"PERHAPS SOMEDAY
I WILL KNOW THE JOY

22:54.807 --> 22:57.007
"OF STANDING WITH YOU

22:57.009 --> 22:59.076
"AS WE CHEER ON THE TIGERS
OR THE CARDINALS,

22:59.078 --> 23:00.911
OR MY BELOVED RED SOX."

23:00.913 --> 23:02.413
-[LAUGHING]
-"UNTIL THEN...

23:02.415 --> 23:04.048
"...I MUST
IMAGINE YOU BESIDE ME,

23:04.050 --> 23:05.483
"INSPIRING IN ME

23:05.485 --> 23:07.718
"NEW WAYS TO WRITE
OF COURAGE AND TRIUMPH,

23:07.720 --> 23:10.521
"OF DIAMONDS AND TRIANGLES...

23:10.523 --> 23:13.057
"OF THE PLACES WE MUST RUN

23:13.059 --> 23:15.126
BEFORE GOING HOME."

23:16.495 --> 23:18.162
"HAVE I GONE MAD, JONATHAN?

23:18.164 --> 23:20.131
"DID I FALL IN LOVE

23:20.133 --> 23:21.665
"WITH A STRANGER

23:21.667 --> 23:23.701
LAST NEW YEAR'S EVE?"

23:23.703 --> 23:24.869
[OLIVER]: "THERE IS NOTHING

23:24.871 --> 23:27.805
CRAZY ABOUT FALLING IN LOVE,
EVEN WHEN--"

23:27.807 --> 23:29.807
[SHANE]: "WHEN SOMETHING
TELLS YOU,

23:29.809 --> 23:31.409
"AGAINST ALL COMMON SENSE,

23:31.411 --> 23:34.578
"THAT YOU HAVE MET THE ONE
YOU'VE BEEN WAITING FOR

23:34.580 --> 23:36.046
ALL YOUR LIFE."

23:36.048 --> 23:39.950
[OLIVER]: "ALL MY LIFE...
AND THEN I LET YOU GO."

23:41.887 --> 23:44.155
[SHANE]:
"WHY DID I LET YOU GO?"

23:46.091 --> 23:48.159
"WHY DID I LET YOU GO?"

23:50.529 --> 23:52.696
[♪]

23:57.135 --> 23:58.502
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

23:58.504 --> 24:01.739
IT IS MY EXTREME PLEASURE
TO WELCOME YOU

24:01.741 --> 24:05.042
TO THE OPENING FESTIVITIES
OF THE 63RD ANNUAL

24:05.044 --> 24:07.611
MISS COLORADO
SPECIAL DELIVERY PAGEANT.

24:07.613 --> 24:09.847
THE JUDGES HAVE
MADE THEIR DECISIONS

24:09.849 --> 24:11.215
AND NOW IT IS TIME TO ANNOUNCE

24:11.217 --> 24:12.515
THE 10 SEMI-FINALISTS

24:12.517 --> 24:14.652
WHO WILL BE COMPETING
IN TOMORROW NIGHT'S PAGEANT.

24:14.654 --> 24:16.053
YAY.

24:16.055 --> 24:18.222
WILL THE FOLLOWING CONTESTANTS
PLEASE STEP FORWARD

24:18.224 --> 24:19.824
WHEN I ANNOUNCE YOUR NAME?

24:21.460 --> 24:23.461
[HUSHED CHATTER]

24:25.564 --> 24:26.697
TIFFANY DELMONICO!

24:26.699 --> 24:27.932
MISS TERMINAL ANNEX.

24:27.934 --> 24:30.067
[APPLAUDING]

24:30.069 --> 24:33.103
TRACY STEADMAN,
MISS BOYD ANNEX!

24:35.841 --> 24:39.109
CARLA NIRNENBARGER,
MISS BONNIE BRAE.

24:40.512 --> 24:43.647
EVELYN NIGHTSMITH,
MISS SNOW MASS VILLAGE.

24:46.151 --> 24:47.551
I'M HERE. I MADE IT.

24:47.553 --> 24:49.920
[RAMON]: WILLOW BARANSKY,
MISS FORT MORGAN!

24:51.590 --> 24:52.957
FINALLY!
WHERE WERE YOU?

24:52.959 --> 24:53.924
I WAS AT THE BANK,

24:53.926 --> 24:55.024
AND THE ALARM WENT OFF,

24:55.026 --> 24:57.027
AND THEY EVACUATED
EVERYONE SO FAST,

24:57.029 --> 24:58.762
THAT I LEFT MY CELLPHONE
ON THE TELLER'S COUNTER,

24:58.764 --> 25:00.898
AND I HAD
TO WAIT FOREVER

25:00.900 --> 25:03.234
BEFORE THE SECURITY GUY
WOULD LET ME BACK IN.

25:03.236 --> 25:04.635
JOANNE APPLETON--

25:04.637 --> 25:05.703
IT WAS
A NIGHTMARE!

25:05.705 --> 25:06.837
[RAMON]: ...MISS EAST AURORA.

25:06.839 --> 25:09.607
JENNIFER RAPAPORT,
MISS TELLURIDE.

25:11.076 --> 25:13.544
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

25:13.546 --> 25:16.113
LESLIE WHITMORE,
MISS CASTLE PINES.

25:16.115 --> 25:20.618
AND NOW, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
OUR LAST SEMI-FINALIST...

25:20.620 --> 25:24.088
THAT LUCKY LADY WHO WILL BE
JOINING THESE OTHER NINE,

25:24.090 --> 25:27.191
ONE OF WHOM WILL BECOME
MISS SPECIAL DELIVERY, IS--

25:27.193 --> 25:28.792
RITA HAYWITH!

25:28.794 --> 25:30.227
MISS DENVER MAIN BRANCH.

25:30.229 --> 25:32.630
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

25:33.932 --> 25:36.000
MISS RITA HAYWITH.

25:38.770 --> 25:40.804
RITA?

25:40.806 --> 25:42.540
[CROWD MURMURING]

25:42.542 --> 25:43.941
[♪]

25:43.943 --> 25:45.309
WELL...

25:47.646 --> 25:49.914
I SUPPOSE
WE HAVE ENOUGH

25:49.916 --> 25:52.650
FOR SOMEONE TO LOCATE

25:52.652 --> 25:56.120
A SPORTSWRITER
NAMED JONATHAN WHO IS...

25:58.123 --> 26:00.057
FOND OF THE RED SOX.

26:00.059 --> 26:01.892
OR A LADY NAMED KATHERINE,

26:01.894 --> 26:04.562
WHO VERY WELL COULD BE
ACROSS THE STREET

26:04.564 --> 26:05.896
AT THE HOTEL
THIS VERY MINUTE.

26:05.898 --> 26:08.566
OR AT HOME WITH JONATHAN
AND THE CHILDREN.

26:08.568 --> 26:10.601
ATTENDING A BALL GAME
TOGETHER.

26:10.603 --> 26:12.903
OR DANCING UNDER THE STARS.

26:12.905 --> 26:14.772
I HOPE THEY'RE DANCING.
[LAUGHS]

26:14.774 --> 26:17.141
[JASON SNORES]

26:19.144 --> 26:20.210
[SNIFFS]

26:23.882 --> 26:26.016
THEY GOT TOGETHER...

26:26.018 --> 26:27.084
RIGHT?

26:27.086 --> 26:28.953
I MEAN, THAT...

26:28.955 --> 26:30.287
MUST BE HOW

26:30.289 --> 26:32.323
ALL THE LETTERS ENDED UP
IN THE SAME BOX.

26:32.325 --> 26:34.291
"WHEREVER YOU KEEP
YOUR TREASURES,

26:34.293 --> 26:36.894
THAT'S WHERE
YOUR HEART WILL BE, TOO."

26:40.198 --> 26:42.633
I HAVE TO KNOW
THAT THEY'RE TOGETHER.

26:43.768 --> 26:46.070
WE ONLY HAVE
THREE LETTERS LEFT.

26:46.072 --> 26:50.708
I HAVE TO READ THESE LETTERS,
IF IT'S THE LAST THING THAT I--

26:50.710 --> 26:52.810
"SWEET KATHERINE...

26:52.812 --> 26:55.779
"SOMETIMES IN THE NIGHT,
WHEN I'M ON THE ROAD...

26:55.781 --> 27:00.250
"IN ANOTHER TOWN,
IN ANOTHER ROOM...

27:00.252 --> 27:02.953
"I HEAR A TRAIN WHISTLE.

27:02.955 --> 27:04.755
"I NEVER KNOW WHERE IT'S GOING,

27:04.757 --> 27:06.790
"BUT I ALWAYS LIE THERE,

27:06.792 --> 27:08.325
"IMAGINING IT'S HEADED WEST,

27:08.327 --> 27:10.894
"TO THE ROCKIES,
TO DENVER...

27:10.896 --> 27:12.663
"TO YOU.

27:12.665 --> 27:15.633
"AND I BLESS THAT TRAIN
AS IT ROLLS BY.

27:15.635 --> 27:18.769
"YOU ARE THE BEST PERSON
I HAVE EVER KNOWN...

27:18.771 --> 27:22.406
"EVEN IF WE HAVE SHARED
LITTLE MORE THAN A KISS

27:22.408 --> 27:25.175
"AND OUR HEARTS
ON A FEW PIECES OF PAPER.

27:25.177 --> 27:29.413
"BUT I HAVE RUN OUT OF WORDS
TO EXPRESS MY LOVE...

27:30.849 --> 27:32.349
"AND I'M RUNNING OUT OF ROAD.

27:34.352 --> 27:37.021
"THE ROAD ENDS WHERE YOU ARE...

27:37.023 --> 27:39.990
"DEAR FRIEND, DEAR LADY,

27:39.992 --> 27:41.692
MY LOVE."

27:45.930 --> 27:47.297
"WILL YOU MARRY ME?"

27:47.299 --> 27:49.800
[♪]

27:49.802 --> 27:51.368
[LAUGHS]

28:00.178 --> 28:02.346
"DEAR SIR...

28:04.916 --> 28:07.751
"I AM WRITING TO YOU
FROM THE BROWN PALACE HOTEL,

28:07.753 --> 28:10.854
WHERE YOUR FRIEND, KATHERINE,
HAS BEEN EMPLOYED."

28:12.157 --> 28:15.225
"SHE HAS DESCRIBED YOU
AS HER FIANCE,

28:15.227 --> 28:18.328
"AND SO I FEEL IT IS APPROPRIATE
FOR ME TO INFORM YOU

28:18.330 --> 28:20.297
"THAT SHE IS VERY...

28:20.299 --> 28:22.399
ILL."

28:25.236 --> 28:29.373
"SHE'S VERY ILL
WITH A RARE FORM OF PNEUMONIA.

28:29.375 --> 28:32.209
HER DOCTORS AT ST. JOSEPH..."
[SIGHS SHAKILY]

28:32.211 --> 28:36.113
"SHE'S TAKEN A TURN
FOR THE WORSE...

28:36.115 --> 28:38.849
THE ENCLOSED... NOTE--"

28:38.851 --> 28:40.818
[♪]

28:49.094 --> 28:51.028
"MY DEAREST JONATHAN...

28:52.163 --> 28:54.898
"WITH THE FEW BREATHS
I HAVE LEFT,

28:54.900 --> 28:56.900
I WANT TO SPEAK WORDS OF LOVE."

28:58.069 --> 29:02.206
"ALL WE'VE EVER SHARED
HAVE BEEN WORDS...

29:02.208 --> 29:04.341
"BUT THEY HAVE BEEN
GOOD WORDS

29:04.343 --> 29:07.044
AND TRUE WORDS.

29:08.313 --> 29:11.482
"AND NOW I AM SENDING
EVERY LETTER YOU WROTE TO ME

29:11.484 --> 29:12.983
BACK TO YOU..."

29:12.985 --> 29:15.285
[♪]

29:15.287 --> 29:18.956
"SO THAT EVEN IF WE CANNOT
BE TOGETHER IN THIS LIFE--"

29:18.958 --> 29:20.457
[SNIFFLES]

29:20.459 --> 29:22.860
"...THE WORDS
THAT WE CREATED TOGETHER

29:22.862 --> 29:25.929
CAN BE KEPT SOMEWHERE
SIDE-BY-SIDE."

29:27.499 --> 29:31.034
"DYING IS HARD, MY LOVE...

29:31.036 --> 29:32.770
"BUT NOT HOPELESS.

29:32.772 --> 29:34.371
"AND...

29:34.373 --> 29:37.941
"AS I WALK THROUGH
THE VALLEY OF THE SHADOW,

29:37.943 --> 29:39.443
"I FEAR NOTHING BUT THE THOUGHT

29:39.445 --> 29:43.547
THAT I MAY HAVE LEFT
ONLY ONE WORD UNSPOKEN--"

29:43.549 --> 29:45.048
[SNIFFLING]

29:45.050 --> 29:46.316
[SOBS]: "YES."

29:47.919 --> 29:50.053
"YES, I WILL BE YOUR WIFE.

29:51.422 --> 29:54.291
"PERHAPS NOT IN THIS LIFE...

29:54.293 --> 29:56.794
BUT IN YOUR HEART."

29:56.796 --> 29:59.363
[GASPS]

30:03.201 --> 30:04.802
"DEAR SIR,

30:04.804 --> 30:09.940
"THANK YOU FOR YOUR LETTER
OF DECEMBER 20TH, '08."

30:12.343 --> 30:15.946
"I AM LEAVING FOR DENVER
IMMEDIATELY,

30:15.948 --> 30:19.850
"AND BY THE TIME YOU READ THIS,
I HOPE TO BE AT HER BEDSIDE.

30:19.852 --> 30:21.552
"IF, FOR ANY REASON,
I AM DELAYED,

30:21.554 --> 30:22.553
"PLEASE TELL HER

30:22.555 --> 30:23.653
"THAT I LOVE HER

30:23.655 --> 30:26.056
"AND I CANNOT SPEND
ANOTHER NEW YEAR'S EVE,

30:26.058 --> 30:27.356
"ANOTHER NEW YEAR'S DAY,

30:27.358 --> 30:31.060
OR ANY OTHER DAY OF MY LIFE
WITHOUT HER NOW."

30:31.262 --> 30:35.065
"TELL HER
TO SWING FOR THE STARS."

30:36.134 --> 30:38.235
"TELL HER TO BREATHE."

30:39.838 --> 30:41.972
"TELL HER TO LIVE."

30:41.974 --> 30:44.041
[WEEPING]

30:44.043 --> 30:46.844
"YOURS TRULY,
JONATHAN WALKER."

30:47.946 --> 30:49.613
[SOBBING]

30:55.620 --> 30:59.122
SHE HAD TO HAVE WRITTEN
ANOTHER LETTER...

31:00.491 --> 31:01.859
[SNIFFS]

31:01.861 --> 31:03.927
THERE'S GOTTA BE
ANOTHER LETTER.

31:05.296 --> 31:06.396
THERE'S GOTTA BE...

31:06.398 --> 31:09.132
ANOTHER LETTER
IN THIS BOX...

31:09.134 --> 31:11.468
[BOX RATTLES]

31:11.470 --> 31:12.469
OLIVER...

31:12.471 --> 31:13.637
SHANE.

31:13.639 --> 31:14.872
OH, SHE...

31:16.007 --> 31:18.909
PLEASE TELL ME
THAT SHE LIVED!

31:18.911 --> 31:19.643
SHE HAD TO
GET THROUGH IT!

31:19.645 --> 31:21.011
SHANE--

31:21.013 --> 31:23.580
I KNOW
THAT SHE...

31:23.582 --> 31:27.217
[WEEPING] SHE--
SHE'S GOTTA BE ALIVE.

31:29.254 --> 31:31.221
SHE'S GOTTA BE ALIVE.

31:31.223 --> 31:32.356
RIGHT?

31:32.358 --> 31:34.524
SHE LIVED?

31:37.228 --> 31:39.963
IT'S OKAY.

31:41.900 --> 31:44.534
I'M SO SCARED.

31:45.603 --> 31:47.437
I KNOW.

31:48.506 --> 31:50.908
I DON'T KNOW--

31:50.910 --> 31:53.110
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO PRAY, OLIVER.

31:53.112 --> 31:54.144
YOU DO.

31:54.146 --> 31:55.679
IT'S OKAY.

31:55.681 --> 31:57.648
-PLEASE?
-I ALREADY HAVE.

32:00.385 --> 32:03.186
COME HERE.

32:03.188 --> 32:04.621
SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH.

32:06.691 --> 32:08.926
[RINGING]

32:12.130 --> 32:13.429
-YEAH.
<i>-WELL, I'LL BE.</i>

32:13.431 --> 32:15.299
THIS IS HOMER FINNEGAN,
THE SECURITY GUARD.

32:15.301 --> 32:16.199
GIVE ME THAT!

32:16.201 --> 32:17.267
<i>-ARE YOU IN THE VAULT?</i>
<i>-HELLO?</i>

32:17.269 --> 32:19.236
[♪]

32:20.538 --> 32:22.339
OLIVER?

32:22.341 --> 32:23.639
<i>NORMAN!</i>
<i>THANK GOD,YOU'RE HERE!</i>

32:23.641 --> 32:25.275
I KNEW IT! I KNEW THIS
WAS WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU!

32:25.277 --> 32:27.144
UH, RITA'S HERE.
DID YOU WANT TO SAY HI?

32:27.146 --> 32:28.345
<i>RITA?</i>

32:28.347 --> 32:29.680
WHY ISN'T SHE
AT THE PAGEANT?

32:29.682 --> 32:32.349
OH, WELL, SHE WAS
WORRIED, TOO.

32:32.351 --> 32:33.617
LIKE ME.

32:33.619 --> 32:35.585
WE WERE... WORRIED.

32:35.587 --> 32:37.387
TOGETHER.

32:37.389 --> 32:39.990
<i>WELL, UH, PLEASE</i>
<i>SEND RITA OUR VERY BEST.</i>

32:39.992 --> 32:43.360
MAY I ASSUME THERE IS
A PLAN TO RELEASE US?

32:43.362 --> 32:45.362
WELL, UH,
I HAVE THIS COUSIN--

32:45.364 --> 32:46.997
-[SHANE GIGGLES]
-HE HAS A COUSIN!

32:46.999 --> 32:49.266
WHO... WHO, UH--?

32:49.268 --> 32:51.501
<i>WHO-- AND I CAN'T</i>
<i>GO INTO DETAILS--</i>

32:51.503 --> 32:53.136
<i>USED TO DO ONE THING,</i>

32:53.138 --> 32:56.039
BUT, UH,
NOW HE DOES ANOTHER,

32:56.041 --> 32:58.141
AND HE HELPS BANKS
TEST THEIR SECURITY SYSTEMS

32:58.143 --> 33:01.378
TO SEE IF THEY'RE SAFE
FROM PEOPLE LIKE...

33:01.380 --> 33:02.378
MY COUSIN.

33:02.380 --> 33:04.514
<i>ANYWAYS, HE'S TALKING</i>
<i>TO THE BANK PRESIDENT</i>

33:04.516 --> 33:05.714
<i>AND THE POLICE AND EVERYBODY,</i>

33:05.716 --> 33:07.317
AND THEY THINK YOU SHOULD BE
OUTTA THERE ANY MINUTE NOW.

33:07.319 --> 33:08.652
[OLIVER]:
<i>"ANY MINUTE NOW"?</i>

33:08.654 --> 33:09.987
BECAUSE, UH,

33:09.989 --> 33:11.521
IF IT'S GONNA BE
A LOT OF MINUTES,

33:11.523 --> 33:12.723
I'M NOT SURE WE CAN
LIVE WITH THAT, NORMAN.

33:12.725 --> 33:13.991
LITERALLY.

33:13.993 --> 33:15.192
OH, NO, YOU'RE FINE.

33:15.194 --> 33:16.994
THE BOOK SAYS YOU'VE GOT
PLENTY OF VENTILATION.

33:16.996 --> 33:18.228
WE'VE GOT PLENTY OF AIR.

33:18.230 --> 33:20.230
ARE YOU SURE?
BECAUSE JASON SAID THAT--

33:20.232 --> 33:21.331
OH, NO, I'M POSITIVE.

33:21.333 --> 33:22.699
THEY KEEP THE ROOM
CLIMATE-CONTROLLED

33:22.701 --> 33:24.468
FOR ALL THE STUFF
THAT THEY KEEP IN THE BOXES.

33:24.470 --> 33:26.103
ISN'T THAT GREAT?

33:26.105 --> 33:27.671
WE'RE CLIMATE-CONTROLLED?

33:27.673 --> 33:31.575
THAT'S NOT
WHAT YOU SAID, JASON.

33:31.577 --> 33:34.578
I MAY HAVE
GOTTEN IT CONFUSED

33:34.580 --> 33:36.780
WITH THE MEAT FREEZER
AT MY OLD JOB.

33:36.782 --> 33:38.048
YOU THINK?

33:38.050 --> 33:39.216
<i>OKAY, SEE YOU SOON.</i>

33:39.218 --> 33:41.084
SO, JASON.

33:41.086 --> 33:42.786
TELL US...

33:42.788 --> 33:46.256
DID YOU FIND
THIS INTERLUDE INSTRUCTIVE?

33:46.258 --> 33:48.158
UM...

33:48.160 --> 33:50.027
SOMETHING ABOUT

33:50.029 --> 33:53.196
BEETHOVEN BEING
A GARBAGE MAN?

33:53.198 --> 33:57.367
"IF A MAN IS CALLED
TO BE A STREETSWEEPER,

33:57.369 --> 34:00.103
"HE SHOULD
SWEEP STREETS SO WELL,

34:00.105 --> 34:01.371
"THAT ALL THE HOSTS OF HEAVEN
AND EARTH

34:01.373 --> 34:03.040
"WILL PAUSE

34:03.042 --> 34:05.142
"TO SAY

34:05.144 --> 34:09.046
'HERE LIVED A <i>GREAT</i> SWEEPER
WHO DID HIS JOB WELL.'"

34:10.481 --> 34:13.050
MARTIN LUTHER KING
SAID THAT, JASON.

34:13.052 --> 34:15.118
AND HE WAS ALSO TALKING

34:15.120 --> 34:18.288
ABOUT ASSOCIATE ASSISTANT
BANK MANAGERS,

34:18.290 --> 34:19.423
AND POSTAL WORKERS,

34:19.425 --> 34:22.092
AND KINGS,

34:22.094 --> 34:23.827
AND PRESIDENTS.

34:23.829 --> 34:26.630
PUT YOUR HEART
IN YOUR WORK, JASON.

34:28.166 --> 34:30.100
BE HAPPY.

34:31.602 --> 34:34.438
[LOCK THUDS]

34:34.440 --> 34:37.240
[GATE RATTLING,
HYDRAULICS HISSING]

34:41.245 --> 34:43.847
AH... THE LIGHT OF DAY.

34:46.350 --> 34:47.851
-[THWAP]
-OH, OLIVER.

34:47.853 --> 34:49.419
HMM?

34:52.090 --> 34:55.225
[♪]

34:59.464 --> 35:00.764
YOU FORGOT THIS.

35:05.870 --> 35:08.605
LADIES FIRST.

35:08.607 --> 35:10.841
[♪]

35:17.148 --> 35:18.181
[DOOR CLACKS OPEN]

35:19.851 --> 35:20.851
OH!

35:22.253 --> 35:23.487
THERE YOU ARE.

35:23.489 --> 35:25.489
OH! ARE YOU OKAY?

35:25.491 --> 35:27.224
I GOT YOU THIS.

35:27.226 --> 35:28.325
OH, FABULOUS.

35:28.327 --> 35:29.726
THANK YOU, NORMAN.
EXCELLENT WORK.

35:29.728 --> 35:31.695
I'D LIKE TO PERSONALLY
THANK YOUR COUSIN

35:31.697 --> 35:32.829
FOR HIS ASSISTANCE.

35:32.831 --> 35:34.731
OH, UH,
THEY HAD TO TAKE HIM BACK.

35:36.501 --> 35:37.734
WHAT WAS
IN THE SAFETY DEPOSIT BOX?

35:37.736 --> 35:39.436
LOVE, NORMAN.

35:40.805 --> 35:42.372
LOTS OF LOVE.

35:42.374 --> 35:43.807
THAT WAS THE SECRET?

35:43.809 --> 35:45.408
[OLIVER]: ALWAYS IS.

35:45.410 --> 35:48.278
AND, RITA, YOU LOOK FANTASTIC.

35:48.280 --> 35:49.412
HOW DID
YOUR RECEPTION GO?

35:49.414 --> 35:50.614
OH, RIGHT!

35:50.616 --> 35:52.415
DID YOU MAKE
THE SEMIFINALS?

35:52.417 --> 35:54.217
OH. I DON'T KNOW.

35:54.219 --> 35:56.286
WE LEFT BEFORE
THEY FINISHED ANNOUNCING THEM.

35:57.355 --> 35:58.755
YOU LEFT?

35:58.757 --> 36:00.223
WHAT? TO FIND US?

36:00.225 --> 36:02.159
OH... FRIENDS

36:02.161 --> 36:03.727
DON'T LEAVE FRIENDS
LOCKED IN BANK VAULTS.

36:03.729 --> 36:05.162
AND WE'RE FRIENDS.

36:05.164 --> 36:06.396
RIGHT?

36:06.398 --> 36:08.231
YES, NORMAN.

36:08.233 --> 36:10.167
WE'RE FRIENDS.

36:10.169 --> 36:13.370
[♪]

36:19.243 --> 36:22.712
[SHANE]: I FEEL
AS THOUGH I KNOW HIM ALREADY.

36:22.714 --> 36:24.648
[♪]

36:24.650 --> 36:26.349
[MAN]: ALL I WANNA DO
IS GO TO THE GAME!

36:26.351 --> 36:28.552
[WOMAN]: THAT'S ALL
YOU EVER DO!

36:28.554 --> 36:30.253
-KATHERINE?
[MAN]: WHAT DO YOU WANNA DO?

36:30.255 --> 36:31.453
[WOMAN]: WHY DO I ALWAYS
HAVE TO THINK OF SOMETHING?

36:31.455 --> 36:33.757
BECAUSE YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO WANTS TO DO SOMETHING!

36:33.759 --> 36:35.258
AND THAT'S MY POINT!

36:35.260 --> 36:36.193
I COME HOME,

36:36.195 --> 36:37.594
I'M TIRED,
AND ALL I WANT IS--

36:37.596 --> 36:38.895
[KNOCKING]

36:38.897 --> 36:40.764
AHEM.

36:44.902 --> 36:46.203
YES?

36:46.205 --> 36:48.305
UH, MR. JONATHAN WALKER?

36:48.307 --> 36:49.339
YEAH, THAT'S ME.

36:49.341 --> 36:50.874
W-WHERE'D YOU GET THAT?

36:50.876 --> 36:53.343
UH, WELL, WE'RE FROM
THE U.S. POST OFFICE AND--

36:53.345 --> 36:54.444
YOU FOUND IT.

36:54.446 --> 36:56.213
[WOMAN]: WHO IS THAT?

36:56.215 --> 36:57.681
IT'S THE POST OFFICE.

36:57.683 --> 36:59.749
THEY FOUND--
THEY FOUND THE BOX.

36:59.751 --> 37:01.284
WELL, THE SHIPPING BOX
WAS DAMAGED,

37:01.286 --> 37:03.820
SO WE HAD TO USE THE KEY
TO OPEN THE DEPOSIT BOX,

37:03.822 --> 37:04.888
TO READ YOUR LETTERS

37:04.890 --> 37:06.623
TO RETURN THIS
TO YOU.

37:06.625 --> 37:07.991
I'M SORRY. OUR LETTERS?

37:07.993 --> 37:08.959
MM-HMM.

37:08.961 --> 37:10.527
YES. YOUR LETTERS.

37:10.529 --> 37:13.930
YOURS AND KATHERINE'S...
LOVE LETTERS.

37:15.967 --> 37:17.567
KATHERINE?

37:17.569 --> 37:19.302
OH, WOW...

37:19.304 --> 37:21.605
LET ME SEE THOSE.

37:27.478 --> 37:29.246
I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D EVER GET TO READ THESE.

37:29.248 --> 37:30.814
THEY'RE NOT YOURS?

37:30.816 --> 37:33.450
NO, I'M JONATHAN WALKER
THE FOURTH.

37:34.685 --> 37:37.520
THESE LETTERS WERE WRITTEN
BY JONATHAN WALKER...

37:37.522 --> 37:38.989
MY GREAT-GRANDFATHER.

37:43.261 --> 37:45.895
[QUIET, ASTONISHED CHUCKLE]

37:45.897 --> 37:48.965
SO MY DAD SHIPPED THIS BOX
TO US JUST BEFORE HE DIED,

37:48.967 --> 37:50.600
AND IT GOT LOST IN THE MAIL.

37:50.602 --> 37:52.402
HE GOT IT FROM HIS DAD
WHEN HE GOT MARRIED.

37:52.404 --> 37:54.371
AND HE GOT IT FROM JONATHAN,

37:54.373 --> 37:57.507
WHO GOT IT AS A WEDDING GIFT
FROM GREAT-GRANDMA KATHERINE.

37:57.509 --> 38:00.343
THEY LIVED.

38:00.345 --> 38:04.347
NOT IN OUR TIME,
BUT THEY LIVED.

38:04.349 --> 38:06.783
AND EVERY WALKER MAN SINCE

38:06.785 --> 38:08.952
HAS GOTTEN THIS BOX
AND THAT KEY

38:08.954 --> 38:10.687
AND THE MESSAGE

38:10.689 --> 38:13.056
THAT THE SECRET TO TRUE LOVE
LIES SOMEWHERE IN THESE LETTERS.

38:13.058 --> 38:14.824
[OLIVER]: BECAUSE
THEY POURED THEIR SOULS

38:14.826 --> 38:16.459
INTO THOSE LETTERS.

38:16.461 --> 38:20.430
AND THEY WERE ALWAYS
KEPT IN A SAFE PLACE.

38:20.432 --> 38:21.898
"WHEREVER YOU KEEP
YOUR TREASURE,

38:21.900 --> 38:24.401
THAT'S WHERE YOUR HEART
WILL BE, TOO."

38:27.471 --> 38:28.605
WHEN WERE THEY MARRIED?

38:28.607 --> 38:29.973
1910?

38:29.975 --> 38:31.508
1909, MAYBE.

38:33.344 --> 38:34.778
1908...

38:34.780 --> 38:36.046
FIRST YEAR
THEY DROPPED THE BALL

38:36.048 --> 38:38.815
IN TIME'S SQUARE
ON NEW YEAR'S EVE.

38:38.817 --> 38:39.883
I FEEL AS THOUGH

38:39.885 --> 38:41.584
I'VE LOST
A KINDRED SPIRIT.

38:41.586 --> 38:44.020
SO I GUESS IT'S
MY TURN TO READ THESE.

38:44.022 --> 38:45.422
OH, I HOPE THAT YOU DO.

38:45.424 --> 38:47.357
BETTER YET,

38:47.359 --> 38:49.025
READ THEM OUT LOUD,

38:49.027 --> 38:50.360
TOGETHER.

38:53.331 --> 38:55.465
[♪]

39:05.776 --> 39:07.110
MISS TELLURIDE,

39:07.112 --> 39:10.814
YOU HAVE 15 SECONDS LEFT
TO COMPLETE YOUR ANSWER.

39:12.116 --> 39:13.750
PASADENA...

39:13.752 --> 39:16.486
91105.

39:16.488 --> 39:18.054
WASHINGTON PARK?

39:18.056 --> 39:19.823
[TELLURIDE]: 80209.

39:19.825 --> 39:21.458
[RAMON]: UPPER WEST SIDE,
NEW YORK CITY.

39:21.460 --> 39:25.895
10023?

39:25.897 --> 39:28.498
THAT IS...

39:28.500 --> 39:29.599
CORRECT.

39:29.601 --> 39:31.835
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

39:31.837 --> 39:33.370
GOOD JOB.

39:33.372 --> 39:35.105
THIS IS GONNA BE REALLY CLOSE.

39:36.574 --> 39:38.441
[RAMON]:
AND FOR OUR FIFTH FINALIST,

39:38.443 --> 39:39.976
CURRENTLY TIED FOR FIRST PLACE,

39:39.978 --> 39:42.746
PLEASE WELCOME
MISS DENVER MAIN BRANCH,

39:42.748 --> 39:44.013
R-R-RITA HAYWITH!

39:44.015 --> 39:46.850
[APPLAUDING]

39:48.652 --> 39:50.954
SHE LOOKS SO BEAUTIFUL.

39:50.956 --> 39:52.155
SHE IS.

39:52.157 --> 39:53.890
MISS DENVER MAIN BRANCH,

39:53.892 --> 39:56.926
ONLY ONE QUESTION
STANDS BETWEEN YOU

39:56.928 --> 39:58.895
AND THE MOST COVETED TITLE

39:58.897 --> 40:01.531
IN THE COLORADO-UNITED STATES
POSTAL SYSTEM.

40:01.533 --> 40:03.166
HERE WE GO.

40:03.168 --> 40:06.002
FOR THE CROWD...

40:06.004 --> 40:08.071
NAME 13
U.S. GOVERNMENT-APPROVED

40:08.073 --> 40:09.706
MODES OF MAIL TRANSPORT.

40:09.708 --> 40:10.940
OKAY.

40:10.942 --> 40:11.941
YOU HAVE
ONE MINUTE.

40:11.943 --> 40:13.176
SHE KNOWS THIS!

40:13.178 --> 40:14.411
OH, NO! WAIT!

40:14.413 --> 40:16.112
OH, SHE ONLY MEMORIZED 12.

40:16.114 --> 40:17.680
YOU'RE KIDDING?

40:19.450 --> 40:21.050
DO THAT THING YOU DO.

40:21.052 --> 40:23.052
PRAY.

40:23.054 --> 40:24.821
[RITA]: UH, CARS, TRUCKS,
TRAINS,

40:24.823 --> 40:26.489
UH, BOATS, FERRIES...

40:27.658 --> 40:28.958
HELICOPTERS...

40:28.960 --> 40:30.527
SUBWAYS,

40:30.529 --> 40:31.828
SEAPLANES...

40:32.897 --> 40:34.197
AIRPLANES,

40:34.199 --> 40:35.832
HOVERCRAFTS...

40:37.701 --> 40:39.836
BICYCLE AND FEET!

40:39.838 --> 40:41.504
[RAMON]: THAT'S ONLY 12.

40:41.506 --> 40:42.806
WE NEED ONE MORE.

40:42.808 --> 40:45.675
UH... OH...

40:45.677 --> 40:46.943
UM...

40:46.945 --> 40:49.746
[♪]

40:51.816 --> 40:53.583
OH! WAIT! MULES!

40:53.585 --> 40:55.518
RELIABLE MULES DELIVER MAIL

40:55.520 --> 40:57.921
TO THE BOTTOM
OF THE GRAND CANYON!

40:57.923 --> 41:00.457
-YES! MISS RITA HAYWITH!
-OH...

41:00.459 --> 41:03.993
YOU ARE MISS COLORADO
SPECIAL DELIVERY 2014!

41:03.995 --> 41:05.128
OH, MY GOSH!

41:05.130 --> 41:07.163
[LOUD APPLAUSE]

41:08.466 --> 41:11.167
[♪]

41:11.169 --> 41:13.236
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

41:13.238 --> 41:14.471
HI!

41:15.973 --> 41:18.575
OH, THANK YOU!

41:18.577 --> 41:21.110
[♪]

41:26.717 --> 41:28.618
[♪]

41:31.222 --> 41:33.990
[RAMON]:
♪ SHE'S MISS SPECIAL DELIV'RY

41:33.992 --> 41:37.126
♪ YES, SHE'S
OUR POST OFFICE QUEEN ♪

41:37.128 --> 41:39.662
♪ FROM ROCKY MOUNTAIN

41:39.664 --> 41:43.066
♪ TO FIELD AND FOUNTAIN
AND EVERY ZIP IN BETWEEN ♪

41:43.068 --> 41:47.237
♪ BY PLANES, TRAINS
BUS, MULE, OR LIVERY ♪

41:47.239 --> 41:49.873
♪ YOU BET SHE'LL GET
THOSE LETTERS THROUGH ♪

41:49.875 --> 41:53.243
♪ SO, HAIL
MISS SPECIAL DELIV'RY ♪

41:53.245 --> 41:55.044
♪ AND ALL THINGS POSTAL

41:55.046 --> 41:56.779
♪ FROM COAST TO COAST'LL SING

41:56.781 --> 41:59.983
♪ SHE'S THE DAMSEL
WE STAMP AND CANCEL ♪

41:59.985 --> 42:03.586
♪ THE HOLY GRAIL
OF FIRST-CLASS MAIL ♪

42:03.588 --> 42:05.555
♪ MISS SPECIAL DELIV'RY

42:05.557 --> 42:10.159
♪ THAT'S YO-O-O-O-O-OU!

42:10.161 --> 42:12.061
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

42:12.063 --> 42:14.264
[♪]
